description: Number of poly-IH73-tiles (holes allowed) with n cells.
comments: Originally from Vicher's table, which lists this as "Puzzle 3".Isohedral tiling IH73 (see Figure 6.2.4 of Grünbaum and Shephard) is obtained from the regular square tiling by replacing the edges of each square by symmetric curves bulging alternately inwards and outwards, so that each modified square now has a rotation of order two and reflections in horizontal and vertical axes as symmetries but no longer has rotations of order four or diagonal reflections as symmetries. - Joseph Myers, Oct 08 2011
references: Branko Grünbaum and G. C. Shephard, Tilings and Patterns. W. H. Freeman, New York, 1987, Sections 6.2 and 9.4.
author: _James A. Sellers_, Aug 28 2000
extensions: Edited and a(11)-a(16) by _Joseph Myers_, Oct 08 2011
